Class CompRational

  • java.lang.Object

    Arithmetic, java.lang.Comparable<CompRational>

    public class CompRational
extends Rational
implements java.lang.Comparable<CompRational>
    Extension of the Rational class that can be used to do arithmetic operations on rational numbers and compare them to each other. The denominator of Rational objects is always positive.

        public int compareTo(CompRational obj)
        Compares this object with the specified object for order. Returns -1 , 0, 1 as this object is less than, equal to, or greater than the specified object. This implementation of compareTo() is consistent with equals, so (x.compareTo(y)==0) == (x.equals(y)).
